    {"id":"FLO_036","question":"Gladiolus is commercially propagated through:","options":["Seeds","Corms","Bulbs","Rhizomes"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Gladiolus is propagated commercially through corms and cormels. Corms produce uniform plants and flowers.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_037","question":"Which flower is known as 'Queen of Bulbs'?","options":["Lily","Tulip","Gladiolus","Dahlia"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Gladiolus is called 'Queen of Bulbs' or 'Sword Lily' due to its sword-shaped leaves and beautiful flower spikes.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_038","question":"Chrysanthemum is a ______ plant with respect to photoperiodism:","options":["Long-day","Day-neutral","Short-day","Intermediate-day"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Chrysanthemum is a short-day plant (SDP), requiring less than 12 hours light for flower initiation. Commercial growers manipulate day length.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_039","question":"The family of jasmine is:","options":["Rosaceae","Oleaceae","Asteraceae","Apocynaceae"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Jasmine (Jasminum spp.) belongs to family Oleaceae. India is the largest producer of jasmine in the world.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_040","question":"French marigold botanical name is:","options":["Tagetes erecta","Tagetes patula","Tagetes minuta","Calendula officinalis"],"answer":1,"explanation":"French marigold is Tagetes patula. African marigold is Tagetes erecta. Both belong to family Asteraceae.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_041","question":"The pigment extracted from marigold used in poultry feed is:","options":["Carotene","Lutein","Lycopene","Anthocyanin"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Lutein (xanthophyll) extracted from marigold petals is used in poultry feed for egg yolk coloring and in food industry.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_042","question":"Copper sulphate is sprayed on rose for:","options":["Disease control","Defoliation","Flower induction","Growth promotion"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Copper sulphate spray at 5% causes defoliation in roses, which is done before pruning to break dormancy and induce new flush.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2020"},
