    {"id":"FLO_044","question":"Which rootstock is commonly used for budding of roses?","options":["Rosa indica","Rosa canina","Rosa multiflora","All of these"],"answer":3,"explanation":"Rosa indica (tropical), Rosa canina (temperate), and Rosa multiflora are all used as rootstocks depending on climate and cultivar.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_045","question":"Orchids growing on tree trunks are called:","options":["Epiphytes","Saprophytes","Terrestrial","Lithophytes"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Epiphytic orchids grow on tree trunks using aerial roots for anchorage and moisture absorption. Dendrobium, Vanda are examples.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_046","question":"The national flower of India is:","options":["Rose","Jasmine","Lotus","Marigold"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Lotus (Nelumbo nucifera) is the national flower of India. It symbolizes purity, divinity, and beauty.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_047","question":"Tuberose (Polianthes tuberosa) belongs to family:","options":["Liliaceae","Amaryllidaceae","Iridaceae","Orchidaceae"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Tuberose belongs to Amaryllidaceae (earlier Agavaceae). It is propagated through bulbs and is an important loose flower crop.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_048","question":"Topiary is a practice of:","options":["Growing trees in containers","Trimming plants into ornamental shapes","Growing climbing plants","Raising hedge fences"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Topiary is the art of training and trimming trees/shrubs into ornamental or geometrical shapes for landscape decoration.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_049","question":"Which type of garden is the Mughal Garden style?","options":["English garden","Formal garden","Japanese garden","Wild garden"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Mughal gardens follow formal/Persian style with geometric layouts, terraces, water channels (char-bagh pattern), and symmetry.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2020"},
    {"id":"FLO_050","question":"Arka Amar is a variety of:","options":["Rose","Tuberose","Chrysanthemum","Jasmine"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Arka Amar is a tuberose variety developed by IIHR Bangalore with high flower yield and fragrance.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_051","question":"Bonsai is the art of:","options":["Growing large trees","Growing miniature trees in containers","Flower arrangement","Rock garden making"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Bonsai (Japanese: bon=tray, sai=planting) is the art of growing miniature trees in shallow containers through pruning and training.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_052","question":"Dahlia is propagated commercially through:","options":["Seeds only","Tuberous roots","Stem cuttings","Both B and C"],"answer":3,"explanation":"Dahlia is commercially propagated through tuberous roots and stem cuttings. Seeds are used only in breeding programs.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_053","question":"Which flower crop has the highest export value from India?","options":["Rose","Orchid","Carnation","Gladiolus"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Rose has the highest export value among Indian flower crops, with major exports of cut roses to European and Middle Eastern markets.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2020"},
    {"id":"FLO_054","question":"Ikebana is:","options":["Japanese flower arrangement","Chinese garden style","Indian garland making","European bouquet"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Ikebana is the traditional Japanese art of flower arrangement, emphasizing form, line, and minimalism.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_055","question":"Crossandra is commonly known as:","options":["Firecracker flower","Kanakambaram","Both A and B","Night jasmine"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Crossandra (Crossandra infundibuliformis) is known as Firecracker flower and Kanakambaram in South India.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_056","question":"The ideal pH for rose cultivation is:","options":["4.5-5.0","5.5-6.5","7.5-8.5","8.5-9.5"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Rose grows best in slightly acidic soil with pH 5.5-6.5, well-drained loamy soil rich in organic matter.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_057","question":"Which plant growth regulator delays senescence in cut flowers?","options":["Ethylene","Silver thiosulphate (STS)","ABA","2,4-D"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Silver thiosulphate (STS) is an anti-ethylene agent used as pulse treatment to extend vase life of cut flowers like carnation.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_058","question":"Gerbera belongs to family:","options":["Rosaceae","Asteraceae","Oleaceae","Liliaceae"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Gerbera (Gerbera jamesonii) belongs to Asteraceae/Compositae. It is grown as cut flower under polyhouse conditions.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_059","question":"Pergola is a:","options":["Water fountain","Covered walkway with climbing plants","Sunken garden","Rock arrangement"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Pergola is an open framework structure over a walkway supporting climbing/trailing plants for shade and beauty in gardens.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_060","question":"Black spot disease of rose is caused by:","options":["Diplocarpon rosae","Sphaerotheca pannosa","Peronospora sparsa","Botrytis cinerea"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Black spot is caused by Diplocarpon rosae, producing circular black spots with fringed margins on rose leaves.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_061","question":"Anthurium is propagated by:","options":["Seeds","Suckers","Both A and B","Bulbs"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Anthurium is propagated by seeds and vegetatively through suckers, stem cuttings, and tissue culture commercially.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_062","question":"Which flower is used for extraction of essential oil called 'attar'?","options":["Jasmine","Rose","Tuberose","Marigold"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Rose attar (Gulab ka attar) is extracted from Rosa damascena petals through steam distillation, mainly in Kannauj, UP.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2020"},
    {"id":"FLO_063","question":"Carnation belongs to family:","options":["Caryophyllaceae","Asteraceae","Rosaceae","Oleaceae"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Carnation (Dianthus caryophyllus) belongs to family Caryophyllaceae. It is one of the top cut flowers commercially.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_064","question":"The practice of growing plants without soil using nutrient solution is:","options":["Aeroponics","Hydroponics","Xeriscaping","Fertigation"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Hydroponics is growing plants in nutrient-rich water solution without soil. Used for commercial flower production in polyhouses.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2020"},
    {"id":"FLO_065","question":"Powdery mildew of rose is caused by:","options":["Diplocarpon rosae","Sphaerotheca pannosa","Puccinia sp.","Cercospora sp."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Powdery mildew of rose caused by Sphaerotheca pannosa (syn. Podosphaera pannosa) produces white powdery coating on leaves and buds.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_066","question":"Lilium belongs to family:","options":["Amaryllidaceae","Liliaceae","Iridaceae","Orchidaceae"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Lilium (lily) belongs to family Liliaceae. It is propagated through bulbs and scales. Asiatic and Oriental hybrids are popular.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_067","question":"Pinching in chrysanthemum is done to:","options":["Increase flower size","Promote branching and more flowers","Delay flowering","Reduce plant height only"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Pinching (removal of terminal bud) promotes lateral branching resulting in more flowers per plant in spray-type chrysanthemums.","difficulty":"medium","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
    {"id":"FLO_068","question":"Which is the largest flower in the world?","options":["Sunflower","Lotus","Rafflesia arnoldii","Victoria amazonica"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Rafflesia arnoldii produces the largest individual flower (up to 1 m diameter), found in Southeast Asian rainforests.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_069","question":"Sucking pest that causes silvering of leaves in rose is:","options":["Aphid","Thrips","Red spider mite","Mealybug"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Thrips (Thrips tabaci) cause silvering/streaking of rose petals and leaves by rasping and sucking cell contents.","difficulty":"hard","topic":"floriculture","source":"ICAR_JRF"},
    {"id":"FLO_070","question":"Avenue trees are planted along:","options":["Roadsides","Inside greenhouses","In pots","In nursery beds only"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Avenue trees (Polyalthia, Cassia, Delonix, Peltophorum) are planted along roadsides for shade, aesthetics, and pollution control.","difficulty":"easy","topic":"floriculture","source":"HPSSC_HEO_2017"},
